## 7. Construction Industry Context & Design References

### Market Positioning
The client is a US-based regional construction firm: home building, excavation, residential + commercial. Not a solo contractor, not a national company. The sweet spot is "established regional builder with a strong agency site." This positions against:
- Solo contractors (too local, no web presence)
- National firms like Turner or Skanska (too corporate, too big)

The "medium rare" brief means: executed with confidence and precision, not overdone. A medium-rare steak has color, texture, substance. Not raw (placeholder-heavy, minimal) and not well-done (overcooked with animations, gradients, gimmicks).

### Top Competitor / Reference Sites

| Site | URL | What to take away |
|---|---|---|
| Turner Construction | turnerconst.com | Dark, confident palette; full-bleed imagery; typographic authority |
| Suffolk Construction | suffolk.com | Horizontal mega-sections; clean hierarchy; no clutter |
| Ryan Companies | ryancompanies.com | Service breakdown with visible pricing context; filterable projects |
| Barton Malow | bartonmalow.com | Premium feel, dark hero, regional warmth |

These are visual mood references only. The demo's design should feel as polished as these, not derivative of them.

### Construction Industry UX Conventions (what clients expect)

- **Video or dramatic hero photo** — now the industry standard; a static all-text hero reads as dated
- **Stats counter ("X projects, Y years")** — near-universal on professional construction sites; instant credibility signal
- **Filterable portfolio** — clients qualify themselves by category; this is the #1 conversion driver on construction sites
- **Pricing transparency** — construction firms that show ballpark pricing convert better; most hide prices (this is a differentiator)
- **Contact form with service type selector** — routes the inquiry; "what service are you inquiring about?" pre-qualifies leads
- **Mobile-first hero** — 55%+ of first visits to construction company sites come from mobile (homeowners researching on phone)

### Font Availability Confirmed
All three Google Fonts families used in the design system are confirmed available:
- Oswald (display, headlines): `https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Oswald:wght@400;600;700`
- DM Sans (body): `https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:opsz,wght@9..40,400;9..40,500;9..40,600`
- Archivo (sub-headings): `https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Archivo:wght@400;600;700;800`

Combined embed (from planner):
```html
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Oswald:wght@400;600;700&family=Archivo:wght@400;600;700;800&family=DM+Sans:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..40,400;0,9..40,500;0,9..40,600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
```

