## 9. Build Flags for demo-builder

1. **Download hero video + poster** to `assets/` as shown in Section 2. Same-origin avoids all CORS and hotlink issues. Use `curl` during build.

2. **Pexels CDN URLs** for the backup/lightbox large images are stable but only for hotlinking (they require a referrer or work as `<video>` src attributes without referrer issues). For `<img>` tags, Pexels images sometimes require a referer header. Stick to Unsplash for `<img>` tags — Unsplash CDN does not require a referer.

3. **Unsplash short-ID URL format** `https://images.unsplash.com/photo-{short-id}?w=800&q=80` should work. If any short-ID URL 404s, visit `https://unsplash.com/photos/{short-id}`, grab the canonical CDN hash from page source (format: `photo-{13-digit-timestamp}-{12-char-hash}`), and use that instead.

4. **video autoplay requires `muted` attribute** in HTML (not just `muted` in JS). Chrome/Safari block autoplay on unmuted video. The planner's code example already includes it.

5. **`loading="lazy"` on all gallery `<img>` tags** prevents blocking the hero paint while gallery images load.

6. **Test filter + lightbox locally** before commit — the `data-filter` CSS approach described in the plan is clean but verify the CSS selector syntax is correct (demo-builder tip: `[data-filter="residential"] .project-card:not([data-category="residential"])` needs the grid container to have the attribute set correctly on filter click).

7. **No em-dashes or en-dashes** anywhere in HTML or JS copy strings. Run a quick text search before commit: `grep -r "—\|–" ../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/construction-company-website/`

8. **`workSamples.js` entry** from the planner is ready to use verbatim. Find the next sequential `id` in the existing file before inserting.

